cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) for the cognitive management of Bandwidth Allocation Models (BAMs) in Multiprotocol Label Switching (MPLS) networks (cs.NI). The proposed approach involves the use of Case-based Reasoning (CBR) for dynamic BAM reconfiguration, which falls under the category of system and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the optimization of network resources, which is related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
